######use nFeature_RNA >2000 and percent.mt < 20 for QC
total <- data.frame( "dataset" = names(all) ,
                     "n_cells_beforeQC" = c(ncol(all$mole),ncol(all$zeng),
                                             ncol(all$Ai),ncol(all$tyser),
                                             ncol(all$xiang),ncol(all$zhou) )

                     )


##check QC 

for (x in 1:length(all) )
{
print(paste( names(all[x]),length(which(all[[x]]$nFeature_RNA >2000 & all[[x]]$percent.mt < 20)  ) ))  
}
## [1] "mole 5240"
## [1] "zeng 14400"
## [1] "Ai 8766"
## [1] "tyser 1194"
## [1] "xiang 551"
## [1] "zhou 4251"
total$n_cells_afterQC <- as.numeric(c(5240, 14400, 8766, 1194, 551, 4251)) 

total$dataset <- factor(total$dataset, levels = c("xiang","zhou", "Ai", "mole", "tyser", "zeng"))

total$n_cells_remove <- total$n_cells_beforeQC-total$n_cells_afterQC
total$reserv.perct <- total$n_cells_afterQC/total$n_cells_beforeQC
total$remove.perct <- total$n_cells_remove/total$n_cells_beforeQC

total<- melt(total)
## Using dataset as id variables
unique(total$variable)
## [1] n_cells_beforeQC n_cells_afterQC  n_cells_remove   reserv.perct    
## [5] remove.perct    
## 5 Levels: n_cells_beforeQC n_cells_afterQC n_cells_remove ... remove.perct
##plot###n_cells before QC
p <- total[which(total$variable=="n_cells_beforeQC"),]
ggplot(data=p, aes(x=dataset, y=value)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity")+ 
  theme(text=element_text(size=30))

##plot###n_cells removed after QC
p <- total[which(total$variable=="n_cells_afterQC"),]
ggplot(data=p, aes(x=dataset, y=value)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity")+ 
  theme(text=element_text(size=30))

##plot###n_cells removed percentage
p <- total[which(total$variable %in% c("remove.perct", "reserv.perct") ),]

ggplot(data=p, aes(x=dataset, y=value, fill=variable)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("orange","grey"))+ 
  theme(text=element_text(size=30))

#######merge##################
merge <- rbind(mole,zeng, Ai, tyser, xiang, zhou)

colourCount = length(unique(merge$Var1))
getPalette = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(17, "Set1"))
## Warning in brewer.pal(17, "Set1"): n too large, allowed maximum for palette Set1 is 9
## Returning the palette you asked for with that many colors
ggplot(data=merge, aes(x=dataset, y=Freq, fill=Var1)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = getPalette(colourCount)) + 
  theme(text=element_text(size=30)) 

######use percentage###########

merge <- do.call(rbind, lapply(unique(merge$dataset), function(x) {
  
df <- merge[which(merge$dataset==x),]
df$perct <- df$Freq/sum(df$Freq)
  
 return(df)
}))


ggplot(data=merge, aes(x=dataset, y=perct, fill=Var1)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = getPalette(colourCount))
